## ParseResult type

The result of parsing - either success (with an offset at which to resume parsing the next thing) or failure. If a failure is fatal, parsing should not continue to try alternative options.

A ParseResult may contain a value that represents the parsed input.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export declare type ParseResult<T> = {
    success: true;
    offset: number;
    value: T;
} | {
    success: false;
    offset: number;
    expected: string[];
    fatal: boolean;
};
```
